00:00:06.900 --> 00:00:09.300
Broccoli and Leek Soup

00:00:09.300 --> 00:00:11.600
Serves: 6

00:00:11.600 --> 00:00:12.800
Ingredients

00:00:12.800 --> 00:00:15.300
1 head of broccoli

00:00:15.300 --> 00:00:18.000
1½ tbsp olive oil

00:00:18.000 --> 00:00:20.400
1½ tbsp butter

00:00:20.400 --> 00:00:25.800
2 leeks, thinly sliced (white part only)

00:00:25.800 --> 00:00:30.200
1 large potato, peeled and cut into small pieces

00:00:30.200 --> 00:00:33.200
1 garlic clove, thinly sliced

00:00:33.200 --> 00:00:37.800
750 ml (3 cups) chicken stock

00:00:37.800 --> 00:00:39.800
1 tsp salt

00:00:39.800 --> 00:00:42.500
½ tsp black pepper

00:00:42.500 --> 00:00:44.000
Directions

00:00:44.000 --> 00:00:49.300
Cut off the broccoli florets, roughly chop and set aside.

00:00:49.300 --> 00:01:00.700
Then peel the outer layer of the stem and chop into small pieces.

00:01:00.700 --> 00:01:09.800
In a large saucepan, heat the olive oil and butter and sauté leeks until soft.

00:01:09.800 --> 00:01:18.300
Add broccoli stems, garlic and potatoes and cook for 2 minutes.

00:01:18.300 --> 00:01:26.400
Add the chicken stock, bring to the boil and season with salt and pepper to taste. 

00:01:26.400 --> 00:01:33.500
Then reduce the heat, partially cover and leave simmering until potato is cooked.

00:01:33.500 --> 00:01:41.300
Add broccoli florets, bring to the boil then leave simmering 10 minutes.

00:01:41.300 --> 00:01:45.500
With a hand blender puree the soup until smooth.

